de.uni_mannheim.informatik.dws.winter.processing

Interface Processable<RecordType>

  • Type Parameters:
    RecordType - the type of elements in this processable
    All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DataSet<RecordType,SchemaElementType>, FusibleDataSet<RecordType,SchemaElementType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FeatureVectorDataSet, FusibleHashedDataSet, FusibleParallelHashedDataSet, HashedDataSet, ParallelHashedDataSet, ParallelProcessableCollection, ProcessableCollection

    public interface Processable<RecordType>
extends Serializable
    Interface for all processable collections. Specifies many data processing operations that are used throughout the framework. Implementing classes decide how to perform the operations, which allows for a replaceable processing environment. Default implementations are ProcessableCollection for single-threaded and ParallelProcessableCollection for multi-threaded processing.
    Author:
    Oliver Lehmberg (oli@dwslab.de)
